trend_summary: Over the sequence, dispersed towns grew outward, filling pockets of former farmland and edging main roads. Built-up footprint enlarged modestly but remains interrupted by large forest and field tracts. Some fields rotated to grass or woodland, while other areas were cleared for cultivation. Overall landscape kept a patchy, green, medium-density, semi-urban character.
notable_changes: Housing estates expanded west of the central axis, replacing cropland.
New industrial/commercial complex emerges near the southeastern edge in later images.
Forest cover increases in the northern quadrant as fields revert to woodland.
Central-east farmland consolidates into larger parcels, reducing hedgerow density.
